status_message:
This week, for the first time in more than two years, the Iraqi army entered Mosul, ISIS' last stronghold in the country. 

Mosul was the first city to be taken by the group when they swept into northern Iraq in the summer of 2014 and it's there that their leader, Abu Bakr-al Baghdadi, announced the creation of his "caliphate". Right now, an estimated 10,000 Islamic State fighters are rumoured to be in the city.

It's here that the Iraqi government intends to break the group as a military power capable of holding territory.

As part of the Mosul operation, some of the surrounding cities have also been liberated, one being the primarily Christian city of Qaraqosh. Reporter Danny Gold travelled to the newly-freed city for TheLADbible, only to find it in ruins, still suffering from nighttime attacks and followed a local man back to the home he was forced to flee two years ago.

This is an eyewitness account of the destruction that ISIS are capable of. This is WIRE: Dispatches By TheLADbible.
link_name: WIRE: Dispatches by theLADbible
